From: Mukul Joshi <mukul.joshi@amd.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Apr 2024 11:32:34 -0400
Subject: drm/amdgpu: Fix leak when GPU memory allocation fails
Git-commit: 25e9227c6afd200bed6774c866980b8e36d033af
Patch-mainline: v6.9-rc6
References: jsc#PED-9898 jsc#PED-10191 jsc#PED-10197 jsc#PED-10226 jsc#PED-10237 jsc#PED-10340 jsc#PED-10852 jsc#PED-11022 stable-fixes
Alt-commit: e53a1713de314204f66cc186a74115ea62407876

Free the sync object if the memory allocation fails for any
reason.

Signed-off-by: Mukul Joshi <mukul.joshi@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm.c
index df58a6a1a67e..7c23ba19af33 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm.c
@@ -1854,6 +1854,7 @@ int amdgpu_amdkfd_gpuvm_alloc_memory_of_gpu(
 err_bo_create:
 	amdgpu_amdkfd_unreserve_mem_limit(adev, aligned_size, flags, xcp_id);
 err_reserve_limit:
+	amdgpu_sync_free(&(*mem)->sync);
 	mutex_destroy(&(*mem)->lock);
 	if (gobj)
 		drm_gem_object_put(gobj);
